"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">c</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>是一个恒定的。</p><p>默认情况下， <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N_r(\mathcal W)"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.085em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">n</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.212em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">r</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">（</span></span> <span class="mjx-texatom"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-cal-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.372em; padding-right: 0.046em;">w</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">）</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>将用模型维度<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="d"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.003em;">D</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>呈指数缩放，因此所产生的界限不会比VC更紧。但是，从概念上讲，这越来越近在咫尺。差异是，覆盖数量仍然将每个子类视为相同，而我们尚未以任何原则性的方式粗糙。</p><h2>单模复杂性</h2><p>不用限制整个模型类，而是研究单个模型的复杂性更加易于处理。单模复杂性的大多数概念都是基于对噪声的敏感性的复杂性的概念：应用于输入的噪声（<strong>余量理论</strong>），将噪声应用于重量（<strong>最小清晰度/平坦度</strong>）以及应用于训练样品的噪声（<strong>算法）稳定性和鲁棒性</strong>）。</p><h3>边距</h3><p>边缘理论研究同名<i>边缘</i>，这是从样本到分类器决策边界的最小距离。边缘越大，分类器对输入数据中的小扰动越强大，那么我们期望它越多地将其推广到新数据。 </p><figure class="image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/k7vju08ta9rb5drwbtrj" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/wqq5t1f0wsxwxbllc66m 144w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/qnoh9nhyzgvhyyx2hmll 224w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/hccrthd6th8x9vx3ffro 304w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/z6t7vq2m4eqw4uqblvtw 384w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/xu9xwfkpazsiaggexfqs 464w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/yjyo2qdpclcoiiig5kuf 544w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/l2j47l3vbuu673wqanu7 624w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/fkjvwsuyo2utghh9mlm9 704w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/u6xxooiucqb1fyonu4vi 784w"><figcaption>较大的边缘，即距决策边界的最小距离，意味着更大的稳健性对噪声。</figcaption></figure><p>这可以追溯到过去的支持矢量机（SVM）的美好时光，您可以明确计算保证金并使用它们来设计更多强大的分类器（请参阅<a href="https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-1-4757-3264-1">Vapnik（1995）</a> ）。使用DNN，计算边缘是棘手的。</p><p>更根本的问题是，“大幅度=更好的概括”对现实模型不存在的假设。您会说以下两个决策边界中哪个概括？ </p><figure class="image"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/jhgf7ckyzxzyw4px8yvu" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/zlj0riaqinszrq0bj3im 144w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/dugmhv6kyzscxa1dmpbx 224w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/fxndaudycb28cv1xnthq 304w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/tmgvd7hzullv3labdnzl 384w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/wiep5iztyqqj9ojo1vnr 464w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/v0obxv9kzglghwsyzowm 544w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/kwirsieon4nsh4iextbh 624w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/negy1kb2fy6dn61fw9ak 704w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/h3qosjwuc3wicmb6ilmw 784w"><figcaption>随着决策界限的复杂性的增加，概括与边缘最大化之间的联系并不是自称的，因为余量理论的假设是。</figcaption></figure><p>边缘理论似乎具有一些解释力，尤其是在具有更简单，更结构化数据的环境中（例如<a href="https://openreview.net/forum?id=QPMfCLnIqf">Mohamadi等，2023年</a>）。研究对输入噪声的敏感性的基本思想仍然是一个很好的观念。只是对边缘的特定关注似乎过分强调了。</p><h3>最小平坦/清晰度</h3><p>边缘理论取决于对输入扰动的鲁棒性应导致概括的直觉，“最小平坦”取决于直觉，即对<i>体重</i>扰动的稳健性应导致概括。 </p><figure class="image image_resized" style="width:67.75%"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/egfs5to90s8ubnsvkepv" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/nrxfkdeh4e7m5ab9u1zm 120w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/cogpoyci6z0vkepgbj5d 240w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/mbgxkymhnbuz1usnra0k 360w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/fvooafvib6r1adueusze 480w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/eniulqfgsjssk6gsyjlg 600w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/ffnpzztuby6dkzw2hdbr 720w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/mjvyncg49man3tp0jhwp 840w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/bjbxw2gzxd4ew1gasgc1 960w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/hlzvjeotny6vpquvnved 1080w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/uG7oJkyLBHEw3MYpT/dnb8zu9zsuhogxnuj2no 1155w"><figcaption>扁平的最小值对重量的扰动更为强大，因此对数据的扰动更加稳健。</figcaption></figure><p>如果损失景观的曲率（由Hessian测量）很低，则重量的较小变化将意味着损失的变化很小。因此，如果我们通过引入新颖的样本（=要求它概括）来消除损失的情况不会改变损失的情况。相反，如果曲率很高，则该模型更为复杂，并且可能概括较差。</p><p>就像深度学习中<s>所有</s>许多想法一样，这可以追溯到<a href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper/1994/file/01882513d5fa7c329e940dda99b12147-Paper.pdf">Hochreiter和Schmidhuber在90年代写的一篇论文</a>。他们提供的直觉基于算法复杂性理论的最小描述长度（MDL）原理。用MDL的语言，指定“平面”最小值的位置所需的位置更少，更简单的功能应更好地概括。</p><p> <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1609.04836">Keskar等。 （2017年）</a>表明，Minibatch SGD会收敛到更扁平的最小值，并且这与概括误差密切相关。但是，<a href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper/2017/file/10ce03a1ed01077e3e289f3e53c72813-Paper.pdf">Neyshabur等人。 （2017a）</a>和<a href="http://proceedings.mlr.press/v70/dinh17b/dinh17b.pdf">Dinh等。 （2017年）</a>指出，这种幼稚的方法是有缺陷的：可以通过重新构度来任意缩放清晰度，并且在随机标签上训练的模型通常比在真实标签上训练的模型通常具有更平整的最小值。为了解决这个问题， <a href="http://proceedings.mlr.press/v139/kwon21b/kwon21b.pdf">Kwon等人。 （2021）</a>提出了<strong>自适应清晰度</strong>，这对于重新构度不变，并且似乎与概括误差良好相关。</p><p>事实证明，自适应清晰度不足以节省清晰度理论。 <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2302.07011">Andriushchenko等。 （2023）</a>发现与经典的直觉，清晰度甚至更智能的重新配置不变性概念<i>相反</i>- 与较大数据集上的变压器中的概括相关。用他们的话来说，“清晰度<i>不是</i>现代环境中概括的良好指标。”</p><p>有一个更基本的问题：<a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/6g8cAftfQufLmFDYT/you-re-measuring-model-complexity-wrong">神经网络是单数的，因此，用抛物面的寄生虫在本地建模损失景观是无效的</a>。研究对重量变化的敏感性需要代数几何形状更先进的工具。</p><h3>算法稳定性和鲁棒性</h3><p>对噪声的敏感性的另一个概念是最终模型对训练集的变化的敏感性。这是<a href="https://proceedings.neurips.cc/paper/2000/file/49ad23d1ec9fa4bd8d77d02681df5cfa-Paper.pdf">Bousquet和Elisseeff（2000）</a><strong>算法稳定性</strong>背后的想法：如果更改训练样本不会改变模型的性能，则经验风险应该具有较低的差异。</p><p>如果学习算法据说具有<strong>统一的稳定性</strong><span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\beta"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.446em; padding-right: 0.007em;">β</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>如果</p><span><span class="mjpage mjpage__block"><span class="mjx-chtml MJXc-display" style="text-align: center;"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\max _i\left\{\left|\ell\left(f_{w(D_n)}(x_i), y_i\right)-\ell\left(f_{w\left(D_n^{\backslash i}\right)}(x_i), y_i\right)\right|\right\} \leq \beta."><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-munderover"><span class="mjx-itable"><span class="mjx-row"><span class="mjx-cell"><span class="mjx-op"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.151em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">max</span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-row"><span class="mjx-under" style="font-size: 70.7%; padding-top: 0.236em; padding-bottom: 0.141em; padding-left: 1.143em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">i</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mrow MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-size3-R" style="padding-top: 1.256em; padding-bottom: 1.256em;">{</span></span> <span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mo" style="vertical-align: -0.718em;"><span class="mjx-delim-v"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">f</span> <span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="line-height: 0.486em; margin-bottom: 0.014em; margin-top: -0.114em;">w</span> <span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">（</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">d</span></span> <span class="mjx-mrow MJXc-space1"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-size1-R" style="padding-top: 0.593em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">n</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base" style="margin-right: -0.06em;"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.519em; padding-bottom: 0.519em; padding-right: 0.06em;">）</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 70.7%; vertical-align: -0.275em; padding-right: 0.071em;"><span class="mjx-texatom" style=""><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">（</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">x</span></span> <span class="mjx-msubsup"><span class="mjx-base"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">i</span></span></span> <span class="mjx-sub" style="font-size: 83.3%; vertical-align: -0.18em; padding-right: 0.06em;"><span class="mjx-mi" style=""><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">）</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">，</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">y</span></span> <span class="mjx-ms